Job Responsibilities:

Handle full set of shipping arrangement for import/export include getting freight quotation, PO processing, Packing List, Export Declaration documents e,g. Certificate of Origin (worldwide) and large volume of data entry;
Work of the preparation, submission, recording & filing of import/export shipping documents;
Prepare daily & monthly Logistics & Inventory report;
Well communication skills with forwarders;
Provide support to ad hoc tasks as assigned.

Requirements:

Form 5 or DSE graduate;
Minimum 3-4 years in related working experience;
Knowledge & experience in import/export procedures and custom declaration regulations including CEPA & TradeLink application;
Factory of plastic field experience is an advantage;
Familiar with EXCEL and MS Office;
Team player, pro-active, willing to meet challenge and learn attitude;
Good command in spoken and written English, Chinese and Mandarin;
Immediate available would be highly preferred.

 We offer 5-day work with attractive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.

 Please send your full resume with availability, current & expected salary to HR Department:

General clerical works/duties at those 2 departments;
Work closely with various internal divisions;
Assist in any ad hoc tasks assigned by the team supervisor.

 Requirements:

F.5 or above;   
1 year relevant working experience;
Familiar with MS Office;    
Proactive and detail-mined, self-motivated and able to work under pressure;
Immediately available is highly preferred. 

Please forward detailed resume stating employment history with expected salary to HR Department. 

All information collected for recruitment purpose only.

Job Descriptions:

Responsible for purchasing & operation activities from business contracts, sourcing, price negotiation, orders, shipment;

Collaborate with sales team and liaise with suppliers to drive on time shipment delivery;
Liaise and support post-contract management activities like handling deliveries discrepancies and monitoring supplier performance;
Handle full set of shipping I/E documents, liaise with supplier and forwarders for shipment schedule and arrangement;
Prepare regular reporting and conduct analysis to support business decisions;
Assist in other ad-hoc assignment as required.

Job Requirements:

Degree holder majoring in Purchasing, Supply Chain Management or other related subjects with at least 2 years related working experience, with background in purchasing field or manufacturing industry will be a plus;

Fluent in spoken and written English & Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin);
Well versed with PC applications, i.e. MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint & Chinese Word Processing;
Patient, detailed-mind, willing to learn, able to work under pressure;
Well-organized with good interpersonal and communication skills;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Planning & Operation Executive.

Benefits:

5-day work (staggered working hours)
Double pay
Discretionary bonus
Group medical
OT pay
Statutory Annual Leave with extra 7 days Company Annual Leave
Bank Holiday
Other Special Leave i.e. Marriage Leave, etc.

We offer competitive remuneration and benefits, holidays, stable working environment to the right candidates. Interested parties please click "Apply Now" and send your full resume with expected salary in MS Word Format to us (Please quote Position Name & Reference No.)

*All personal data collected will be kept strictly confidential and used for recruitment-related purpose only.

Responsibilities:

Support and deliver the Training Delivery Guide in Customer Relationship Management (CRM) Training;
Collaborate with Regional, Country Sales, and Customer Service teams to determine and evaluate their training requirements and effectiveness, as well as generate and distribute reports;
Participate in the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for Customer Relationship Management (CRM) and assist in guiding designated users among the region.

 Requirements:

Bachelor Degree in any discipline, major in shipping, logistics or business management is highly preferred;
Minimum 10 years of relevant experience;
Strong interpersonal skills such as communication and listening;
Technical skills including a competent understanding of customer service department workflows;
Experience in training or teaching is a must;
Willingness to learn and keep improving the knowledge;
Knowledge in CRM system (preferably Salesforce) is an advantage but not a mandatory requirement;
Familiar with Microsoft Office or Google suite, e.g. Word, Excel, PowerPoint, G-sheets, G-Docs, G-Slides;
Good command in spoken and written English and Chinese, Mandarin is a plus.

Requirements:-


HKCEE/HKDSE or above / Higher Diploma
3 years plus relevant working experience in shipping department of a trading company;
Liaise with factories, shipping companies and Internal teams to arrange shipment and documents;
Responsible for handling import/export documents, shipment and logistics arrangement, Letter of Credit, CTN Application, COC, Inspections, etc;
Experience in managing independently documents for Nigeria is an Advantage;
Good Command of both English and Mandarin is a MUST;
Proficiency in PC application and MS office;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Immediate available is preferred.

Company offers attractive remuneration package including 5-day work, 12 days AL + Banking holidays, Medical benefit, Double pay to the right candidate.  Interested parties please email us your full resume in MS Word or PDF format including the date of availability, current/last & expected salary.


