We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data provided by  job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within eight weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months. A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request by contacting our Human Resources Division.

Requirement:

a) A Hong Kong bachelor's degree, or equivalent;
(b) Good command of written Chinese and English, met the language proficiency requirements of Level 3^ or above in Chinese Language and English Language in the Hong Kong Diploma of Secondary Education Examination (HKDSEE) or in the Hong Kong Certificate of Education Examination (HKCEE), or equivalent, and be fluent in English and Cantonese;
(c) Have at least 5 years of post-qualification full-time work experience in executive and/or anagement duties. Working experience and/or knowledge in the operations of the shipping industry is highly preferred;
(d) Good understanding of government measures against COVID-19 will be an asset;
(e) Sound knowledge in common computer applications and operations including Microsoft Word, Excel Spreadsheet and mail merge as well as Chinese word processing (Candidates may be required to take computer proficiency test and/or written test);
(f) Good organisation, communication and interpersonal skills, and ability to work independently and effectively under tight schedule; and
(g) Candidates must be permanent residents of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region at the time of appointment.
^For appointment purpose, 'Grade C' and 'Grade E' in Chinese Language and English Language (Syllabus B) in the HKCEE before 2007 are accepted administratively as comparable to 'Level 3' and 'Level 2' respectively in Chinese Language and English Language in the 2007 HKCEE and henceforth.


Duties:

report to Senior Manager (Port)
To handle workload incurred in the implementation of the latest anti-epidemic measures for the maritime industry, particularly COVID-19 testing for high-risk and high-exposure groups relating to the staff of designated container terminals and ship services sector.

Mainly deployed for duties relating to COVID-19 testing, duties include –
(a) collect and compile information and data;
(b) maintain databases, registration lists and distribution lists, etc.;
(c) liaise with service providers, industry stakeholders and government departments, etc. for returns and reports;
(d) handle enquiries from the industry and the public through phone, email, etc.;
(e) provide general administrative support; and
(f) undertake any other duties as assigned.


Interested parties, please send your resume in WORD format, stating HKCEE/HKALE/DSE result and availability and clicking APPLY NOW

